    "3), PGD results in the largest GE under the GE AR metric.",
    "This is due to the absence of an explicit penalty in its objective, unlike methods such as TRADES and MART, which incorporate additional penalties to stabilize training and improve generalization.",
    "This empirical result corresponds to our theoretical analysis in Thm. 2.",
    "The AT with a penalty over the distance between softmax before and after perturbation effectively enhance the smoothness for the objective function.",
    "Additional results in Appendix."
